Materials: Boc‐protected PEGylated Squalene (SQ‐PEG1500‐NH‐Boc) was obtained and characterized as in our previous study;
[28]
 Flucytosine (5FC) Pharmaceutical Secondary Standard C.R.M. (Supelco, USA); tetrahydrofuran (THF) anhydrous ≥99.9 % (Sigma‐Aldrich, Germany); N,N‐dimethylformamide (DMF) anhydrous 99.8 % (Sigma‐Aldrich, Germany); methylene chloride (DCM) puriss ≥99.9 % (Honeywell, Riedel‐de Haen, Germany); n‐hexane 99 % (J.T.Baker, Germany); triethylamine (TEA) >99 % (TCI, Germany); sodium chloride (NaCl) ACS >99 % (Honeywell | Fluka, USA); Potassium chloride (KCl) ReagentPlus ≥98 % (Honeywell | Fluka, USA); anhydrous magnesium sulfate (MgSO4) ≥99.5 % (Sigma‐Aldrich, Japan); sodium phosphate dibasic dihydrate (Na2HPO4 x 2H2O) puriss 98.5–101 % and sodium phosphate monobasic monohydrate (NaH2PO4 x H2O) ACS ≥98 % were purchased from Honeywell | Fluka, Germany; double‐distilled water (dd‐H2O) obtained with an FiSTREEM Cyclon WSC044.MH3.4 system, ultra‐pure water (mQ‐H2O) obtained with an TKA‐GenPure 08.2204 system. All chemicals were utilized in their original purchased state without undergoing any purification process.
